html
    head
        title Timestamp microservice
        link(rel="stylesheet" href="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.3.6/css/bootstrap.min.css")

    body
        div(class="container")
            h1(class="header") API Basejump: Timestamp microservice
            blockquote User stories:
                ul 1) I can pass a string as a parameter, and it will check to see whether that string contains either a unix timestamp
                | or a natural language date (example: January 1, 2016)
                ul 2) If it does, it returns both the Unix timestamp and the natural language form of that date.
                ul 3) If it does not contain a date or Unix timestamp, it returns null for those properties.
            h3 Example usage:
            code #{host}/December%2015,%202015
            a(href='/December%2015,%202015') [Show in browser]
            br
            code #{host}/1450137600
            a(href='/1450137600') [Show in browser]
            h3 Example output:
            code
                .
                    {
                    "unix": 1450137600,
                    "natural": "December 15, 2015"
                    }
            br
            br
